title.narrative: CROSS BORDER HA AND COORDINATION (GAZ.)

description.narrative: UNICEF provides an effective and timely cross border humanitarian response & partnerships & Cluster Coordination support within the WoS Turkey Hub in line with relevant Security Council resolutions, under the framework of the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP., which contributes to Child Health, Child Protection And Emergencies, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Education In Emergencies, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Health And Emergencies, Nutrition And Emergencies, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Wash And Emergencies. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: GRP2 2016-17: MENA Country Offices and the RO are empowered to deliver timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.
